%[text] # Power Requirements of Liquid Cooled Data Center
%[text] Copyright 2026 The MathWorks, Inc.
%[text:tableOfContents]{"heading":"Table of Contents"}
%[text] ## Setup Data Center Model
%[text] Create a 6MW data center, with 12 racks, by running the command below. The created data center is combined with a cooling distribution unit, CDU, to complete the model. The framework for this model is derived from Simscape Fluids™ product example [Data Center Cooling](https://in.mathworks.com/help/hydro/ug/data-center-cooling.html). The resulting model is saved as the `DataCenterCooling` SLX file in this project. To re-create the data center used in this example, run the sample code below in the MATLAB Command prompt. Use `getDataCenterNamePlateRatingTable` function to change the default name plate rating for the servers.
%[text] ```matlabCodeExample
%[text] % Specify name of the model.
%[text] DatacCenterModelName = "liqCooled6MWdatacenter";
%[text] 
%[text] % Specify path to save the model library files
%[text] libFileSavePath = fullfile(currentProject().RootFolder,"Workflow","HVAC","DatacenterLiquidCooling");
%[text] 
%[text] % Specify data center server nameplate rating.
%[text] data = getDataCenterNamePlateRatingTable(...
%[text]     Mass=simscape.Value(30,"kg"),...
%[text]     Display=true);
%[text] 
%[text] % Create data center
%[text] createDataCenterWithEnclosure(NumPDUunitsX=3,NumPDUunitsY=4,...
%[text]     ModelName=DatacCenterModelName,...
%[text]     ModelOption="Thermal",...
%[text]     ModelEnclosure=false,...
%[text]     RatingDatacenter=simscape.Value(6000,"kW"),...
%[text]     ServerNamePlateRating=data.nameplateRating,...
%[text]     ServerPowerSystemSpec=data.powerSystemSpecs,...
%[text]     ThermalRes=simscape.Value(1e-6,"K/W"),...
%[text]     Diagnostics=true,...
%[text]     SaveAtFullPath=libFileSavePath);
%[text] ```
%[text] For the above data center model, the coolant distribution unit (CDU) piping is attached to simulate liquid cooling of the 12 racks. The thermal node **H** of the data center is connected to the thermal node **H** of the **CDU Pipe Layout**. Each rack is cooled with a separate pipe and all pipes have a common distributor pipe for flow inlet and outlet.
%[text] Open the model.
open_system("DataCenterCooling");
%[text] Confirm data center rating.
getCompositeDataCenterRating(BlockPath="DataCenterCooling/DataCenter/Datacenter",... %[output:group:07ae16b6] %[output:2f4b3366]
                             Display=true); %[output:group:07ae16b6] %[output:2f4b3366]
%%
%[text] ## Run Simulation
sim(DataCenterCooling);
%%
%[text] ## Calculate Power Requirement
simRes = getDataCenterPowerLossSummary(MeasurementData=measurement_DataCenterCooling);
%[text] The chart below shows the average power requirement due to liquid cooling.
piechart([value(simRes.avgAuxLosses_kW.compressor,"kW");... %[output:group:21404c90] %[output:6f1c3eea]
          value(simRes.avgAuxLosses_kW.condenser,"kW");... %[output:6f1c3eea]
          value(simRes.avgAuxLosses_kW.chiller,"kW");... %[output:6f1c3eea]
          value(simRes.avgAuxLosses_kW.fan,"kW")],... %[output:6f1c3eea]
          ["compressor";"condenser";"chiller";"fan"],... %[output:6f1c3eea]
          Title=strcat("Aux. Losses [",num2str(round(value(simRes.avgAuxLosses_kW.total,"kW"),1))," kW]"),... %[output:6f1c3eea]
          LabelStyle="namedata",... %[output:6f1c3eea]
          DisplayOrder="ascend"); %[output:group:21404c90] %[output:6f1c3eea]
%[text] Plot component temperature.
figure("Name","Component Temperature"); %[output:34a944ce]
plot(simRes.result.Time,value(simRes.temperature_degC.ambient,"degC")); %[output:34a944ce]
hold on; %[output:34a944ce]
plot(simRes.result.Time,value(simRes.temperature_degC.serverRackMax,"degC")); %[output:34a944ce]
hold on; %[output:34a944ce]
plot(simRes.result.Time,value(simRes.temperature_degC.serverCoolantOutlet,"degC")); %[output:34a944ce]
hold on; %[output:34a944ce]
plot(simRes.result.Time,value(simRes.temperature_degC.coolingTowerOutlet,"degC")); %[output:34a944ce]
hold on; %[output:34a944ce]
plot(simRes.result.Time,value(simRes.temperature_degC.condenserOutlet,"degC")); %[output:34a944ce]
hold on; %[output:34a944ce]
plot(simRes.result.Time,value(simRes.temperature_degC.evaporatorOutlet,"degC")); %[output:34a944ce]
hold off; %[output:34a944ce]
legend(["Ambient",... %[output:34a944ce]
        "Server (max)",... %[output:34a944ce]
        "Coolant - server outlet",... %[output:34a944ce]
        "Coolant - cooling tower outlet",... %[output:34a944ce]
        "Coolant - condenser outlet",... %[output:34a944ce]
        "Coolant - evaporator outlet"],Location="bestoutside"); %[output:34a944ce]
xlabel("Time"); %[output:34a944ce]
ylabel("Temperature (degC)"); %[output:34a944ce]
%[text] Close model.
close_system("DataCenterCooling");

